        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 18 at 12:49PM CDT by NWS Paducah KY</headline>
        <description>At 1245 PM CDT, local emergency management reported several
sightings of a funnel cloud from a rain shower that is east of
Bernie. The shower was nearly stationary.

HAZARD...Funnel cloud sighting.

SOURCE...Emergency management.

IMPACT...They are usually very brief and do not normally touch the
ground.

Locations impacted include... Bernie.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

Conditions are favorable for the development of weak, brief funnel
clouds. This type of funnel cloud is usually harmless, but on rare
occasions they can briefly touch down, producing wind gusts over 50
mph. If a funnel cloud is spotted move indoors and report your
sighting to the National Weather Service.

This storm may intensify, so be certain to monitor local radio
stations and available television stations for additional information
and possible warnings from the National Weather Service.</instruction>
